comments.name: PR10IV
comments.text: L10I/V are polymorphic, PI-selected accessory mutations that increase the replication of viruses with other PI-resistance mutations.

comments.name: PR74S
comments.text: T74S is a PI-selected accessory mutation that is polymorphic in most non-B subtypes.

comments.name: RT103N
comments.text: K103N is a non-polymorphic mutation that confers high-level reductions in NVP and EFV susceptibility. It is the most commonly transmitted DRM.

comments.name: RT179I
comments.text: V179I is a polymorphic mutation that is frequently selected in persons receiving ETR and RPV. However, it has little, if any, direct effect on NNRTI susceptibility.
